    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "TOLEDO, Ohio \u2013 The Toledo baseball team scored a season-high 21 runs to pick up a series-opening, 21-5 win over Northern Illinois on Friday afternoon at Scott Park in seven innings.\nThe Rockets (8-10, 4-0 MAC) have won their last five games and mark their best MAC start since 2009. UT used an 11-run first inning to take an early lead and never looked back, adding insurance runs in the second, fourth and fifth innings for the run-rule victory.\nSeven Rockets tallied multi-RBI contests while four players had multi-hit outings. Two players had perfect days at the plate as\nCharlie Scholvin\nand\nJacob Payne\neach went 2-for-2. Scholvin plated four runs and knocked in two RBIs while Payne had three RBIs and drew three walks. Liam Arisch went 3-for-4 at the plate while adding four RBIs and scoring two runs.\nNathan Leininger\n(W, 3-0) tossed 6.1 innings, allowing five runs on five hits and striking out nine in a winning decision.\nArturo Ormaza\ncame in for relief, tossing the final two outs and adding a strikeout.\nToledo will look to win the series tomorrow, with first pitch at 1:00 p.m. at Scott Park.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"Proud of the way we attacked today. The wind was howling but we didn't let that affect anything. We played well in all three phases of the game. The hitters continued to build innings and have good at-bats all day long. With tough conditions, Nate Leininger shined today and kept a really powerful NIU offense at bay. Tomorrow is a new day and we need to keep the focus on the things that have allowed us to play some good baseball the past couple weeks.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 2-for-2, 2 RBI, 4 R, 1 BB\nJacob Payne\n\u2013 2-for-2, 3 RBI, 1 R, 3 BB\nLiam Arsich\n\u2013 3-for-4, 4 RBI, 2 R, 1 BB\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 2-for-4, 2 RBI, 3 R, 1 BB\nCole Meyer\n\u2013 1-for-2, 2 RBI, 2 R, 1 BB\nPitching Lines\nNathan Leininger\n(W, 3-0) \u2013 6.1 IP, 5 H, 5 R, 5 BB, 9 K\nArturo Ormaza\n\u2013 0.2 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 1 BB, 1 K\nHow It Happened\nUT\u00a0plated\u00a011 runs in the bottom of the first\u00a0off of six hits, two walks and a hit by pitch.\nCharlie Scholvin\nhad two RBIs in the inning.\nThe first five Rockets reached in the bottom of the second inning, as the Rockets added five more runs to extend their lead, 16-1.\nAn RBI single from\nJacob Payne\nand an RBI double from\nLiam Arsich\nin the fourth inning helped Toledo add three more runs to its lead, 19-1.\nCole Cahill\nknocked a two-RBI single to right field in the fifth inning to extend the lead, 21-1.\nNorthern Illinois rounded out the scoring with a run in the sixth and three more in the seventh."
